{
  "model_version": "m1-ieee1838-computable-v4",
  "case_id": "v4_4die_3d_stack",
  "description": "v4 4-die 3D stack benchmark with per-die BIST engines and mandatory task-based model per IEEE 1838 Section 0.4 corrected physical model. FPP is NOT on every die -- only die0 and die2 have FPP hardware; die1 and die3 use serial TAP only. Each die with BIST gets its own independent engine, enabling simultaneous BIST execution across dies.",
  "provenance_notes": [
    "v4 task model: test_objects declare mandatory test_types and transport_options, not recipe picks.",
    "FPP per-die: only die0 and die2 have FPP lanes physically connected. die1 and die3 use serial TAP only. This is the real IEEE 1838 model -- FPP is optional (Clause 7), not every die has it.",
    "Per-die BIST engines: each die with BIST-capable targets gets its own engine (capacity=1 per engine), mimicking real hardware design.",
    "TAP time-multiplexing: serial TAP is the only shared bottleneck; BIST tasks release TAP during local execution, enabling interleaving.",
    "DWR segment lengths and FPP lane counts are model assumptions aligned with industrial 3D stack dimensions.",
    "Thermal RC parameters are proxy values suitable for relative comparison between algorithms."
  ],
